external_knowledge:
- 'Periods' in the periodic table can be seen as stages of knowledge accumulation in chemistry;
- 'Milestones' metaphorically refer to periods with increasing discovery of elements;
- The average rate metaphorically represents the speed at which new knowledge (elements) has been added to the periodic table after 1930.

sql:
SELECT symbol
FROM elements
WHERE electronegativity = (SELECT MAX(electronegativity) FROM elements);

SELECT name, atomic_number
FROM elements
WHERE atomic_number IN (
    (SELECT MIN(atomic_number) FROM elements),
    (SELECT MAX(atomic_number) FROM elements)
);

SELECT symbol, name, atomic_number, atomic_mass
FROM elements
WHERE atomic_number = (SELECT MIN(atomic_number) FROM elements);

external_knowledge:
- "attic of the periodic table" refers to elements with atomic numbers greater than 50;
- "more than half a century of discovery behind them" means the elements were discovered before the year 2000;
- "significant weight in their atomic cores" means the atomic mass is greater than 50.0;
- "shown their face before the dawn of the new millennium" refers to being discovered before the year 2000;
- "elecronic appeal recorded" refers to having a recorded electronegativity property.

